video:video.video:title: Hawaii Snorkeling
video:video.video:description: http://www.to-hawaii.com/snorkeling.php Hawaii is a snorkeling paradise. No matter where you are in Hawaii, you will find excellent snorkeling beaches all over.

video:video.video:title: Olomana - Like A Seabird In The Wind and Hi`ilawe

video:video.video:description: Tunnels Beach has some of the best snorkeling and diving on the entire island of Kauai. As you can see in this video there is little shade on the beach, so it is good to bring your own beach umbrella. Visit http://www.to-hawaii.com/kauai/beaches/tunnelsbeach.php for information and photos about Tunnels Beach.

video:video.video:title: Tunnels Beach, Kauai - video 2
video:video.video:description: Great snorkeling and diving in the crystal clear waters of Tunnels Beach.

video:video.video:title: Anini Beach, Kauai
video:video.video:description: This is Anini Beach, located on Kauai's north shore. It is a beautiful beach.

video:video.video:description: Poipu Beach is one of the most popular beaches on Kauai. It offers good swimming conditions and has a large park area, including picnic tables, pavilions, and a playground.

video:video.video:description: This video shows Poipu's white sand and beach area.

video:video.video:description: http://www.to-hawaii.com/big-island/beaches/kealakekua-bay.php Few other spots have as much historical meaning as Kealakekua Bay.

video:video.video:title: Kealakekua Bay, Big Island

video:video.video:description: http://www.to-hawaii.com/big-island/beaches/puakobay.php Puako Bay has a rocky shoreline with many tide pools, inlets and coves, which offer good snorkeling conditions when the ocean is calm.

video:video.video:title: Lanikai Beach, Oahu
video:video.video:description: Lanikai Beach is on Oahu's windward coast, south of Kailua Beach Park. Offshore are the Mokulua Islands, Moku Nui and Moku Iki. Visit http://www.to-hawaii.com/oahu/beaches/lanikaibeach.php for information and photos about Lanikai Beach.

video:video.video:title: Mokulua Islands, Oahu
video:video.video:description: Popular kayaking destination, located off of Lanikai Beach on Oahu's windward coast.

video:video.video:description: Home to the Iao Needle rock formation and surrounded by lush vegetation.

video:video.video:title: Hanalei Bay, Kauai - video 2

video:video.video:title: Driving in Princeville, Kauai - video 1
video:video.video:description: Very beautiful and upscale town on Kauai. If you don't stay there, it is worth it to drive through, but don't park anywhere on the side of the road because this is not allowed and they will tow your car. There are only very few and small public parking lots. All other parking areas are private and for hotel and resort guests.

video:video.video:title: Driving in Princeville, Kauai - video 2
video:video.video:description: Beautiful and upscale Kauai resort town.

video:video.video:title: Kilauea Lighthouse, Kauai - video 1
video:video.video:description: The video is taken from the Kilauea Lighthouse lookout point, where you can get a good overview of the lighthouse. If you want to go closer to the lighthouse, you have to drive a short distance down a steep road (no pedestrians are allowed on this road). There is an entrance fee as well.

video:video.video:title: Kilauea Lighthouse, Kauai - video 2
video:video.video:description: Scenic view from Kilauea Lighthouse toward a seabird sanctuary. In the background, you can hear some construction noise. When we visited, some work was being done on the lighthouse :( But the lighthouse needs it. It looks really old.

video:video.video:title: Kilauea Lighthouse, Kauai - video 3
video:video.video:description: Looking towards Secret Beach and Kauai's northern coastline.

video:video.video:description: http://www.to-hawaii.com/big-island/beaches/holoholokaibeachpark.php This is not your typical picture-perfect white-sand beach. The rocky strip of coastline boasts something completely different.

video:video.video:title: Puako, Big Island
video:video.video:description: http://www.to-hawaii.com/big-island/cities/puako.php Pukao's main attraction is its large collection of intricate petroglyphs carved into volcanic rocks.

video:video.video:description: Leprosy (Hansen's disease) patients lived in exile here between 1866 and 1969. Saint Damien, a Belgian missionary priest, took care of these people until he contracted the disease himself.

video:video.video:title: Napili Bay, Maui - video 1

video:video.video:description: This beach is also known as the beach of broken necks and bones. The shorebreak is very powerful. Red warning flags are present year-round. It's a popular bodyboarding beach, but is only for experts. This was on a relatively calm day.

video:video.video:title: Nukolii Beach, Kauai - video 2
video:video.video:description: Splashing waves, black lava rocks and surrounded by green vegetation - a picture perfect beach on Kauai.

video:video.video:title: Kauai Coffee Company - video 2

video:video.video:title: Video of Iceland volcano eruption, giant ash clouds from Grimsvotn
video:video.video:description:
Iceland's imposed a flight ban and closed its main airport after the country's most active volcano, Grimsvotn, erupted. It lies under the uninhabited Vatnajokull glacier in southeast Iceland and has been dormant for 7 years. A large plume of smoke and ash is stretching 20 km into the air. Iceland's Meteorological Office says that the eruption at the Grimsvotn volcano has been accompanied by a series of small earthquakes. Scientists have been expecting a new eruption and have said previously that this volcano's eruption will likely be small and should not lead to the air travel chaos caused in April 2010 by ash from the Eyjafjallajokul volcano.
